  "text": "How long does it take to solve the elliptic curve discrete logarithm problem (ECDLP) on a given elliptic curve using given hardware? This question was addressed recently for the Koblitz curve defined in the Certicom challenge ECC2K-130 for a variety of hardware platforms [2] This paper zooms into Section 6 of [2] and describes the implementation of the parallel Pollard rho algorithm [CITATION_1] for the Synergistic Processor Elements of the Cell Broadband Engine Architecture (CBEA) in detail. We discuss our choice to use the technique of bitslicing [CITATION_2] to accelerate the underlying binary-field arithmetic operations by comparing a bitsliced to a non-bitsliced implementation.",
